Add the missing environment variables to the prowjob container spec in the prowjob.json file:
{
  "name": "AZURE_BLOB_CONTAINER_NAME",
  "value": "capz-e2e-blob-container"
},
{
  "name": "IMAGE_TAG_ACR_CREDENTIAL_PROVIDER",
  "value": "v0.12.0"
}

These values should be added to the container's environment section in the prowjob specification at the path: /spec/template/spec/containers[0]/env

Add the missing environment variables to the Prow job's pod_spec.containers.env section in prowjob.json:
{
  "name": "AZURE_BLOB_CONTAINER_NAME",
  "value": "your-container-name"
},
{
  "name": "IMAGE_TAG_ACR_CREDENTIAL_PROVIDER",
  "value": "your-acr-credential-provider-tag"
}
Verify by re-running the test to ensure the variables are correctly applied and cluster creation proceeds.
